Kingdom Holding Drops Most in Two Years on Failed Bid

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-02-19T09:43:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-19/kingdom-holding-drops-most-in-two-years-on-failed-bid-correct-.html
(Corrects headline to show bid was for Zain.)    Kingdom Holding Co . dropped the most
in more than two years after saying it has not reached an
agreement with Mobile Telecommunications Co. to buy the Kuwait-
based company’s 25 percent stake in Zain Saudi Arabia.  Kingdom’s shares dropped 9.8 percent, the biggest intra-day
decline since December 2008, to 9.20 riyals at 11:50 a.m. in  Riyadh .  The deadline for Kingdom’s offer expired at 5 p.m. on Feb.
16, the Riyadh-based company said in a statement posted on the
Saudi bourse’s website today.  Zain Saudi’s shares declined as much as 6.8 percent, the
most in three weeks, to 7.55 riyals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  